               <p>JEFFERY JOLLY. I am a <rs id="t18291029-224-viclabel1270" type="occupation">paper-stainer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-224-victim1847 t18291029-224-viclabel1270"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18291029-224-crimeloc1271">Marylebone</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-224-crimeloc1271" type="placeName" value="Marylebone"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-224-crimeloc1271" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-224-off1268 t18291029-224-crimeloc1271"></join>. I have known the prisoner in the trade - he came to me on the 15th of September, and said he had a job for a gentleman who had sold his house, and must have it papered immediately, and wanted some patterns; I gave him some - he came the next day, and said the gentleman had selected one - I gave him to understand there would be no credit; I called one of my lads, and told him to take the papers to the gentleman, but not leave them without the money; I gave him a receipt - the prisoner said the gentleman's name was Sorlter, and his own name was 
               <persName id="t18291029-224-person1848">
                  John 
                  Brown
               <interp inst="t18291029-224-person1848" type="surname" value="Brown"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-224-person1848" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-224-person1848" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-224-person1849">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COOPER
               <interp inst="t18291029-224-person1849" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-224-person1849" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-224-person1849" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent by the prosecutor on the 15th of September, with twelve pieces of paper; he told me not to leave them without the money - I went with the prisoner, and when we got to the house he said he had known Mr. Jolly many years, and he would call in the evening and pay the money; I left the paper in the kitchen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-224-person1850">
